      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FWIW, SkGifCodec handles this by never passing the stream to the base class SkCodec. With a null stream, rewindIfNeeded simply returns true.\n\nBut you\u0027re right; we wouldn\u0027t want to rewind if we\u0027re just decoding the next frame.\n\nIt\u0027s probably more logical to put this inside handleFrameIndex, given the current architecture, although SkCodec does not currently keep track of \"I most recently decoded frame i\", which would be necessary to skip this call to rewindIfNeeded.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 350,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 370,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
