      "writtenOn": "2018-08-01T22:48:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My point was subtle. The superclass\u0027 SkCodec::rewindIfNeeded method doesn\u0027t just rewind the stream and call this.onRewind. It also does:\n\n    // startScanlineDecode will need to be called before decoding scanlines.\n    fCurrScanline \u003d -1;\n    // startIncrementalDecode will need to be called before incrementalDecode.\n    fStartedIncrementalDecode \u003d false;\n\nDo I also want to be doing that here, by calling SkCodec::rewindIfNeeded?",
      "parentUuid": "2da2fdbf_5a030328",
