      "message": "Yeah, but the timing doesn\u0027t work:\n\n----\n\nUser calls SkCodec::startIncrementalDecode, which sets fStartedIncrementalDecode \u003d true\n\nUser calls SkCodec::incrementalDecode a first time, which needs fStartedIncrementalDecode \u003d\u003d true\n\nSkCodec::incrementalDecode calls SkWuffsGifCodec::onIncrementalDecode\n\nNow, if I call the superclass\u0027 SkCodec::rewindIfNeeded here, instead of just rewinding the stream myself, it\u0027ll set fStartedIncrementalDecode \u003d false\n\nUser calls SkCodec::incrementalDecode a second time, which needs fStartedIncrementalDecode \u003d\u003d true. Boom!\n\n----\n\nNot sure exactly what to do here, but I added a rambling TODO to SkCodec::rewindIfNeeded to not forget about it. :-)",
      "parentUuid": "ad79b494_032c62a5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 429,
