      "message": "I don\u0027t think you\u0027re missing any std::moves. But you do need to have a move constructor. SkWebpCodec does this (and stores its frames directly in its vector), and you\u0027d need a similar one here:\n\n    SkWuffsGifFrame(SkWuffsGifFrame\u0026\u0026 other)\n        : INHERITED(other.frameId())\n        , fReportedAlpha(other.fReportedAlpha)\n    {}\n\nYou could actually simplify both of these by adding a move constructor to SkFrame:\n\n    SkFrame(SkFrame\u0026\u0026) \u003d default;\n\nThen you can default yours, too:\n\n    SkWuffsGifFrame(SkWuffsGifFrame\u0026\u0026) \u003d default;",
